This species has been recorded from the boreal waters of the Northeast Atlantic ( Calder 2012 ) to Galicia, NW Spain ( Ramil 1988 , as
Clytia sp.
) and also from Newfoundland to Cape Cod in the West Atlantic ( Calder 2012 ). Its presence outside the Atlantic Ocean, including the Mediterranean Sea, is considered as doubtful by Calder (2012) . The records from Chile ( Leloup 1974 ;
Galea et al. 2009
) are based on misidentifications ( Galea & Schories 2012 ). Its bathymetric distribution extends from 20 ( Calder 2012 ) to 950 m ( Peña Cantero & Horton 2017 ).
Clytia gigantea
is reported here for the first time from the South Atlantic, at Valdivia Seamount.
